Interface Table<K,V>

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    SortedTable<K,V>

    public interface Table<K,V>
    An interface of table that maps keys to values. No duplicate keys are permited. No null key is allowed.

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • put

        V put(K key,
      V value)
        Put a key-value pair into the table. If the key is already existed, replace it with new value.
        Parameters:
        key - The key with with the specific value is associated.
        value - The speicific value associated with the key.
        Returns:
        The previous value assicated with the key if existed, or else null.

        Retrive the value to which the key is mapped.
